  "prompt": "What are some good young hard rock artist similar to bands like Rage Against The Machine, Wakrat, Foo Fighters, Downset, ACDC and Xombie etc?",
  "response": "If you're looking for young hard rock artists with a similar vibe to bands like Rage Against The Machine, Foo Fighters, and others you mentioned, here are some recommendations:\n\n1. **GRETA VAN FLEET** - With their classic rock sound and powerful vocals, they pay homage to the roots of rock while bringing a modern edge.\n\n2. **METEORA** - This band combines hard rock with elements of nu-metal, drawing inspiration from the early 2000s rock scene.\n\n3. **BAD WOLVES** - Known for their heavy sound and socially conscious lyrics, they have a style reminiscent of bands like Rage Against The Machine.\n\n4. **RIVAL SONS** - This band has a bluesy, hard rock sound that brings a classic feel while still appealing to modern audiences.\n\n5. **DES ROCKS** - Blending rock with punk and alternative influences, Des Rocks brings a high-energy performance and catchy hooks.\n\n6. **STARCRAWLER** - With a gritty, rebellious attitude, their music combines punk and hard rock elements that fans of older bands will appreciate.\n\n7. **DREAM WIFE** - A punk rock trio with an anthemic sound, they bring a powerful message with an energetic live performance.\n\n8. **THE HU** - This Mongolian band fuses traditional throat singing and instruments with hard rock, creating a unique sound that's hard-hitting and fresh.\n\n9. **BAND-MAID** - A Japanese rock band with a strong presence that mixes elements of hard rock and metal, known for their technical musicianship.\n\n10. **MAMMOTH WVH** - The solo project of Wolfgang Van Halen, this music draws from classic rock influences while having a contemporary sound.\n\nThese artists capture the spirit of hard rock and blend various influences, making for some exciting new music in the genre!",
